title: Cairo-based MoneyFellows, which digitizes money circles or rotating savings and credit associations, raised a $31M Series B, bringing its total funding to $37M (Tage Kene-Okafor/TechCrunch)
description:
Tage Kene-Okafor / TechCrunch:
Cairo-based MoneyFellows, which digitizes money circles or rotating savings and credit associations, raised a $31M Series B, bringing its total funding to $37M  —  Egyptian fintech Money Fellows has raised $31 million in what it describes as the first close of its Series B investment.
